Polish Stocks: CEZ, Bank Handlowy, Jastrzebska Shares Move

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-09-16T15:48:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/polish-stocks-cez-bank-handlowy-jastrzebska-shares-move.html
Poland ’s WIG20 Index climbed for a
fourth day, increasing 14.53, or 0.6 percent, to 2,298.52 in
Warsaw, posting the longest run of gains in almost two months.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Bank Handlowy SA (BHW PW), majority-owned by Citigroup
Inc., rose for a third day, adding 5.1 zloty, or 8 percent, to
68.8 zloty. ING Groep NV said Handlowy is “the best Polish bank
stock to invest” in, citing dividends and “quite good”
lending volumes.  Jastrzebska Spolka Weglowa SA (JSW PW) climbed 4 zloty, or
4 percent, to 104 zloty, its fourth day of gains. The Polish
coking-coal producer will join the WIG20 Index after today’s
session, replacing  CEZ AS (CEZ) , the largest Czech power utility,
according to a Warsaw bourse statement on Aug. 8.  CEZ (CEZ PW) lost 6 zloty, or 4.5 percent, to 128 zloty,
retreating for a second day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw 
